---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import ArtsySection from '../components/ArtsySection.astro';
import InteractiveMap from '../components/InteractiveMap.astro';
import Timeline from '../components/Timeline.astro';
import AgentsOfChange from '../components/AgentsOfChange.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';

const SITE_TITLE = "The Gowanus Art Spine";
const SITE_DESCRIPTION = "Transforming congestion into a thriving, creative community corridor.";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
	<body>
  		<Nav />
		<main>
			<!-- HERO SECTION -->
			<header class="hero container reveal">
				<div class="hero-content sharp-border uneven-clip-2 skew-left interactive-hover">
					<h1>The Gowanus Art Spine</h1>
					<h2>From Congestion to Connection</h2>
					<p>An urban intervention addressing gentrification and the displacement of local artists by connecting studios and anchors along a vibrant, community-focused path.</p>
				</div>
			</header>

			<div class="container">
				<!-- INSIGHTS -->
				<div class="reveal">
					<ArtsySection id="insights" className="skew-right">
						<h3><span class="marker-highlight">Insights</span>: The Challenge</h3>
						<div class="split-layout">
							<div class="text-content">
								<p>Gowanus is facing a critical turning point. New residential builds now command a 35% rent premium, creating a financial incentive for landlords to evict artists and convert historic warehouses into luxury spaces.</p>
								<p>Artist studios are an "invisible" asset. Unlike retail storefronts, they don't fit the traditional Business Improvement District (BID) toolkit because they generate low foot-traffic. Every year during Open Studios, hundreds of artists voice fears of displacement and rezoning anxiety.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="image-grid">
								<img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/before-1.png`} alt="Gowanus Congestion 1" />
								<img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/before-2.png`} alt="Gowanus Congestion 2" />
							</div>
						</div>
					</ArtsySection>
				</div>

				<!-- TRANSFORMATION -->
				<div class="reveal">
					<ArtsySection id="transformation">
						<h3><span class="marker-highlight">Transformation</span>: The Intervention</h3>
						<div class="split-layout reverse">
							<div class="text-content">
								<p>Our solution is the <strong>Gowanus Art Spine</strong>, funded by a new <strong>"Congestion Relief" Pricing</strong> model—but for gentrification.</p>
								<p>As new residents move into luxury builds, they pay a one-time fee that goes directly towards building the Art Spine. This curbs gentrification claims and funds cultural preservation.</p>
								<p>Unlike the High Line—which led to displacement and was heavily influenced by private donors—the Art Spine is a community-prioritized pathway designed to increase foot traffic to artist studios without accelerating displacement.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="image-grid">
								<img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/after-1.png`} alt="Art Spine Transformation 1" />
								<img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/after-2.png`} alt="Art Spine Transformation 2" />
							</div>
						</div>
					</ArtsySection>
				</div>

				<!-- PREDICTION (INTERACTIVE MAP) -->
				<div id="prediction" class="reveal">
					<InteractiveMap />
				</div>

				<!-- CONSENSUS (TIMELINE) -->
				<div id="consensus" class="reveal">
					<Timeline />
				</div>
				<div class="reveal">
					<AgentsOfChange />
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>

		

		<footer class="site-footer reveal">
			<div class="container">
				<p><strong>The Gowanus Art Spine</strong> &mdash; UDS26 Team 1</p>
				
				<div class="sources">
				<h5 class="sources-title">Sources</h5>
				<ol class="sources-list">
					<li>
					<a href="https://esd.ny.gov/gowanus" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						Empire State Development (ESD) Gowanus Neighborhood Mixed-Income Housing Development Program
					</a>
					— Over 5,300 expected incoming units filed since the 2021 rezoning.
					</li>
					<li>
					<a href="https://data.census.gov/profile/New_York,_New_York?g=160XX00US3651000" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						U.S. Census Bureau — New York City Profile
					</a>
					— Estimates 2.3 people per household in NYC, projecting ~12,000 new renters in the area.
					</li>
					<li>
					<a href="https://www.brickunderground.com/rent/gowanus-new-development-construction-rentals-condos-brooklyn-ny" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						Brick Underground — "New development is rapidly transforming Gowanus" (May 2025)
					</a>
					— New rental buildings in Gowanus (built 2018 or later) command a 35% rent premium over older buildings, at $77.42/sq ft on average.
					</li>
				</ol>

				<div class="fee-note">
					<strong>Congestion Relief Fee estimate:</strong> 12,000 projected new residents × $200 one-time fee per person = <strong>~$2.4 million</strong> towards the Art Spine Fund.
				</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</footer>

		<script>
			// Intersection Observer for scroll animations
			document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
				const reveals = document.querySelectorAll(".reveal");
				
				const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
					entries.forEach(entry => {
						if (entry.isIntersecting) {
							entry.target.classList.add("active");
							// Optional: Stop observing once revealed
							// observer.unobserve(entry.target);
						}
					});
				}, {
					threshold: 0.1,
					rootMargin: "0px 0px -50px 0px"
				});

				reveals.forEach(reveal => {
					observer.observe(reveal);
				});
			});
		</script>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem 2rem;
		text-align: center;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	.hero-content {
		background-color: var(--color-dark);
		color: var(--color-bg);
		padding: 4rem;
		max-width: 900px;
	}

	.hero-content h1 {
		color: var(--color-bg);
		text-shadow: 4px 4px 0px var(--color-secondary);
	}

	.hero-content h2 {
		background-color: var(--color-accent);
		color: var(--color-bg);
		transform: rotate(2deg);
	}

	.hero-content p {
		margin: 0 auto;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	.split-layout {
		display: flex;
		gap: 3rem;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.split-layout.reverse {
		flex-direction: row-reverse;
	}

	.text-content {
		flex: 1;
	}

	.image-grid {
		flex: 1;
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 2rem;
		position: relative;
	}

	.image-grid img {
		width: 100%;
		aspect-ratio: 1;
		object-fit: cover;
		transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.175, 0.885, 0.32, 1.275);
		z-index: 1;
	}

	.image-grid img:nth-child(2) {
		transform: translateY(2rem) rotate(3deg);
		z-index: 2;
	}

	.image-grid img:first-child {
		transform: rotate(-2deg);
	}

	.image-grid img:hover {
		transform: scale(1.08) rotate(0deg);
		z-index: 10;
		box-shadow: 12px 12px 0px var(--color-secondary);
	}

	.site-footer {
		background-color: var(--color-dark);
		color: var(--color-bg);
		text-align: center;
		padding: 2rem 0;
		margin-top: 6rem;
		border-top: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-accent);
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.split-layout, .split-layout.reverse {
			flex-direction: column;
		}
		
		.hero-content {
			padding: 2rem;
		}
	}
	.sources {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
		padding-top: 1.5rem;
		text-align: left;
		max-width: 800px;
		margin-left: auto;
		margin-right: auto;
	}

	.sources-title {
		font-family: var(--font-heading);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		opacity: 0.6;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}

	.sources-list {
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
	}

	.sources-list li {
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		opacity: 0.75;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.sources-list a {
		color: var(--color-accent);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 2px;
	}

	.sources-list a:hover {
		opacity: 1;
		color: var(--color-secondary);
	}

	.fee-note {
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		opacity: 0.75;
		background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
		padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
		border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
	}

	.fee-note strong {
		color: var(--color-accent);
	}
</style>
